social_posts.post_text: Fun sesh with the boys at JAM!
Join me on my descent into madness. This is one of my favorite aspects of parkour and freerunning. Don’t give up, the struggle is what makes you better.
What a year! I am so excited to see what is coming in 2023 🔥

HAPPY NEW YEARS! My New Years resolution last year was to start a business. I never thought it would be baking protein energy cookies 😂. Now @flipcookiez is in full swing! I just made a discount code ONLY FOR TODAY “IWANTCOOKIEZ” for 30% off everything! This is the time to try it out!! Thank you all for the support!
You guys haven’t seen my face in a while and probably wanna keep it that way, but I’m a rebel.
Gym sesh with the boys. I would take out the pads but I enjoy my back not hurting.

Bits and boops ☔️
@tempestfreerunning
When you go back east and there’s no gym.
This house conjured us back.
Hey guys, I’m not feeling too great today. So I’m gonna lift my spirits with some special moments with cute animals.

Today is my actual 26th birthday! The longest day of the year! This year has had it’s ups and downs and I wanna thank the people that have helped me through it! I’m excited to see what’s planned for the future! ❤️
I had so much fun at the Adrenaline event! I’m a night owl and this was the perfect place for us. I can’t wait for the next one!
Great session with the team! I love when people cheer you on in LA 💕
Wow what a concert. Great friends, Paramore, Billie Eilish, and most importantly HAYLEY WILLIAMS 🔥
What I’ve been doing during the first California Hurricane in 80 years!
Bips and bops from Loyola the other day 🔥

It’s time for a garbage dump of photos just for you 🙏

Honestly I haven’t posted something in a while so here is what the past months have been comprised of ❤️❤️
Halloween will not know what hit them. 🎃Please give me a caption! Also anyone know what my costume is? *bike not included
Our names are Ashton and Corbin, and we like to party.
The name’s Heimer… Barbenheimer. And yes, my legs are as smooth as butter.

What a year this has been. So many ups and downs. I’m very grateful for the same people that have been in my life through the years. They have made my life better in so many ways and helped me through the pitfalls. I am very lucky to have these people in my life. Happy Thanksgiving everybody! 🦃
Dusting off some rust on these moves and got a couple new ones! Also I have a pretty big update on an injury I’m dealing with right now. The video is now up on YouTube!

Just lost my uncle yesterday. I’ve been taking care of him with my family the last few weeks. He fought cancer tooth and nail. He was the funniest person in our family, an am-pro surfer, a performer, and a little bit of a conspiracy theorist which made dinners interesting. However at the end of the day, he was a very loving father to my little cousin. I can’t believe you’re not here anymore. I’ll see you every time I’m at the beach! Love you Uncle Erik.
